{
    "Description": "<h3>Usage</h3><pre class=\"ql-syntax\" spellcheck=\"false\">iguana.messageId()\n</pre><ul><li>Returns the unique identifier for the message currently being processed by the component.</li><li>This ID is commonly used to associate log entries (e.g., via <code><a href=\"@iguana.log\" target=\"_blank\">iguana.log</a></code> or <code><a href=\"@iguana.logInfo\" target=\"_blank\">iguana.logInfo</a></code>) with a specific message.</li></ul><p><br></p><h3>Notes</h3><ul><li>The returned ID is in the format <code>\"&lt;component ID&gt;-&lt;epoch timestamp&gt;-&lt;sub-millisecond ID&gt;\"</code></li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\">The component ID is the ID of the component that enqueued the message using <code><a href=\"@queue.push\" target=\"_blank\">queue.push</a></code></li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\">The epoch timestamp is a timestamp with millisecond precision.</li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\">The sub-millisecond ID is an incrementing integer value. It is used to distinguish messages when multiple messages are received in the same millisecond.</li><li>This value is only available once the message enters the queue. If the script is not triggered from a queued message, this function will return <code>nil</code>.</li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\">This means in translator, this function will return either <code>nil</code> or <code>\"0-0-0\"</code>.</li><li>This ID is specific to Iguana and is not related to HL7 message control IDs or other external identifiers.</li></ul><p><br></p><h3>Returns</h3><ul><li>A unique Message ID string in the format <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">\"&lt;component ID&gt;-&lt;epoch timestamp&gt;-&lt;sub-millisecond ID&gt;\"</code>. <em><u>(string)</u></em></li><li>Or <code>nil</code> if no message is being processed. <em><u>(nil)</u></em></li></ul><p><br></p><h3>Example</h3><pre class=\"ql-syntax\" spellcheck=\"false\">-- Run the component to exercise this code. In translator, calling \n-- iguana.messageId() will return nil if the component is a source \n-- or \"0-0-0\" otherwise.\nlocal MsgId = iguana.messageId()\niguana.log(\"Starting processing\", MsgId)\n</pre>",
    "Name": "iguana.messageId",
    "Parameters": null,
    "ParameterTable": false,
    "SummaryLine": "Retrieves the message ID of the current message being processed."
}